review_blob: Poured it down the drain.  Horrible. Medicine and crap all swished around. Forget aging or buying it. it sucks!

I liked it. Solid milk Stout.  Tried it head to head to left hands and Ill say I thought this had better color and aroma and that better depth of flavor.  Would by=uy this again.  A six pack of this by a summer campfire in Humbolt would settle me in to a grand nights sleep.
 (Read others comments for flavor notes)

Weird! Not an IPA; not a Red. Alcohol is hidden.  Carbonation is minimal.  Did I like it...well...Ill drink the 3 bombers I bought, unless aguest wants one.  Would fit well  with a burger or italian sausage.
This is damn near perfect.  Smooth, hoppy, malty, tasty.  Tried it back to back with SN Bigfoot and am hard pressed to pick a favorite btwn the two, but I choose this.
sorely disappointed.  Off flavor, horrible smell. Im letting the other I have sit for a long time before I try this again.
2005 This was great.  I love the barley wine and this one is excellent.  Great color, smooth tasty lots of hops.
Dark malty sugary sweet.  Great looking. stong tasting. cant believe Ive never had this. Would love to get it again. (even Age it)

Id like to sit down and drink this with an arrogant bastard...they seem very similar.  Tons of flavor, very dry, Shit load of hops...a side by side blind tasting would be a thousand times more fun than Pepsi vs Coke
2003: Good beer, Red amber color, little to no head, smooth sweet carmel overtones, subtle malt, liked it would rathar have aged it longer.

I just got back from Pacific Coast (oakland brewery), and brought home a bottle of their new holiday beer.  I had it last night and enjoyed it, but, unfortunately, I had it after I was near black-out...(I love their leviathan, toooooooo much)...I do remember the brewer, a very nice guy I always shoot the shit with, saying "let me know what you think. And watch out! I used a little champagne yeast; so open it slowly and away from your face." I do remember, lots of lacy bubbles, good head, strong candy flavor ("sweet tart" esque), noticable alc, but no need for an eye patch.
beer_name: Pacific Coast Holiday Trappist Style Ale

review_blob: Bottle:  This was fricking great...Black as night, creamy chocolate head, A little too much carbonation (very very think foam).  Sweet, smokey, cocco overtones.  I can wait for bottle # 2...

Bottle # 50 (2004) I wasnt impressed.  There were tons of little chapagne bubbles lining the glass.  White head lingered.  Reddish amber hazy color. Sweet spicy aroma. It tasted thin.  Sweet with orange undertones and a touch spicy.  Need time to develop.  Ill cellar #49 for a while and try it again.
beer_name: Pizza Port Double Overhead Abbey Ale

review_blob: 2004 bottle - Malty!  Long lasting head - off white.  Cloudy brown (looked like liquid milk chocolate)  Dry malty flavor.  Needs time to sweeten A bit wooden or smokey flavor (couldnt tell which)  Finished with light molassas undertones.

2002.  Thick creamy head with a few large lingering bubbles. Reddish Carmel color.  Very strong sweet aroma.  Hints of coffee and caramel under strong malt flavor.  Extremely bitter.  Aftertaste was still extremely bittler a few minutes later.  Put a few bottles away and will try this again in 6 months.

MOderately flavorful...hints of citris below banana.  Rocky white foam that fizzed quickly. Amber-orange color.  Sweet-moderately.  Lovely buttery mouth feel with a lingering taste and texture.  enjoyed it, would buy it again.  Will cellar it for future consideration.

Great Beer...I used to live with one of the brewers.  He was the best roommate in history.  Drank dank beer and always brought a keg home on friday...Even one made a beer especially for me (the Pentagram Ale-a kitchen sink beer with 14+ alc.)  If ya meet Robert Fevior, tell him" Animal sent me"...Anywho...
Black Opaque color (black holeesque) with a mocha head.  Very thick beer, viscus.
Malty coco aroma, lots of chocolate (as you would expect) creamy and smooth with a very full mouth feel.  FInish is Dry and crisp...WHats missing is its longevity.  THe first couple of slugs are full and rich, but by the end of the bomber its taste flattens out and seems less special...not a chore but less special.  
Buy it. its good.

2004
 - Aroma= pleasing-hint of hops and overt malt
-Appearence=Mahogony, hint of copper reds, little head, white, mostly diminishing
-Initial Flavor= sweet, hops and malt, hints of spice
-Finish= bitter, Carmel, metalic, a bit astringent, Lingers
-mouth feel=Drying and creamy

Overall = Not their best.  Thier best was 2001 and 2003 a close second.  Dont know if they change recipies or just labels every year, but maybe my tastes change every year.  Next year I will get another 6 pack and hopefully unlike this year, go back for more every shopping trip in Dec.

I LOVE THIS BEER.  Forget a review...listen to this.  The bay area (S.F.) had a shortage.  I wanted this so bad this year.  Every Bev and Mo. was sold out.  Stone gave me the distributers number, but he was sold out.  every store on his list was sold out.  So i called Beer of the month...Son of a gun...they had plenty.  They shipped up 6.  I paid the $10+ shipping and got ripped.  It was a happy day
What is there to say...perfect.  Strong hops, no balance what so ever, just strong hops.  Dry, Crisp. Perfect

i like this but not as much as the "Big Daddy"
Good dark carmel amber color. Good mouth feel. Good hop. Good beer...not great. Good
I always go to this as my :go to Ale".  When I need just 1 more six pack.  this is it. Copper color, citris over tones. Top notch company.

Quality Beer...Great flavor begining to end...Tons of Hops (not Stone tons, but tons), fruit flavors are very sweet, like some else wrote "candy-esque" Full mouth feel. would like to leave this aside for a year and try it again to see what flavors arise.  Solid to Great beer
